/**
 * Runs the full P8-A → P8-D intelligence stack for every active workflow
in the authenticated workspace, then feeds all results into the P8-E
comparative-intelligence engine to produce a workspace-level risk ranking.

For each workflow the engine computes:
  • comparativeRiskScore (0–100) — blend of rWC + projected complexity +
    trend bonus + fragility bonus + hotspot bonus × confidence multiplier
  • workspaceRank — 1-based rank within the workspace (1 = highest risk)
  • operationalPriority — informational | watch | elevated | urgent | critical
  • trendDirection, fragilityLevel, confidenceLevel — from P8-C / P8-D

Workspace-level analytics:
  • WorkspaceHotspotConcentration — dominant workflow count, concentration
    ratio, chronic hotspot count, critically-degrading count

comparativeRiskScore formula:
  base = rWC × 0.35 + projectedComplexity × 0.25   (max 60)
  trendBonus: critically_degrading=20 | degrading=10 | stable=0 | improving=-5
  fragilityBonus: critical=15 | high=10 | moderate=5 | low=0
  hotspotBonus: min(hotspotCount × 1.0, 5)
  confidenceMultiplier: high=1.0 | moderate=0.90 | low=0.80
  score = clamp(round(subtotal × multiplier), 0, 100)

Ranking semantics:
  Sort: comparativeRiskScore DESC. Tie-break: workflowId ASC.
  Escalation: critically_degrading trend OR critical fragility → +1 priority level.

READ-ONLY — never mutates workflow definitions, governance history, or executions.
Deterministic comparative analytics only — no autonomous actions, no ML.

 * @summary Cross-workflow comparative intelligence & risk ranking for the workspace (P8-E)
 */
